Detailed Description of Procedure

1.	Follow this process to replace a disk…

 https://support.oracle.com/epmos/faces/DocumentDisplay?_afrLoop=124531555921363&parent=SrDetailText&sourceId=3-31042055381&id=1435946.1&_afrWindowMode=0&_adf.ctrl-state=yj2bnadj6_21


2.	If the above procedure fails, as it has done twice on ODA usprora10pn1/usprora10pn2, attempt the following fix

1.	Remove Entries from both /etc/multipath.conf
2.	Oakcli stop oak (on both nodes)
3.	Oakcli start oak on Node 1
4.	After 5 mins, oakcli start oak on node 2
5.	oakcli show ismaster - should show Master on Node 1
6.	Multipath -r
7.	Multipath -F
8.	Multipath -v3
9.	Multipath -ll
10.	On Master Node: oakcli reinit e0_pd__04
 
[root@usprora10pn1 etc]# oakcli reinit e0_pd_04
 
Are you sure you want to reinitialize the disk? : 'e0_pd_04'? [yes/no] : 
yes
Re-initializing the Disk, please wait …
 
